text: construct a PLpgSQL stored procedure to erase records in Procedures where Name equals or is greater than para_Name and Code is para_Code.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Name text, para_Code integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN DELETE FROM "Procedures" WHERE "Name" >= para_Name AND "Code" = para_Code; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _, _ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN DELETE FROM _ WHERE _ >= _ AND _ = _; END; $$;

text: create a stored procedure in PLpgSQL to multiply Event_ID by para_Event_ID in news_report table if para_Event_ID is less than 1000.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Event_ID integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF para_Event_ID < 1000 THEN UPDATE "news_report" SET "Event_ID" = "Event_ID" * para_Event_ID; END IF; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF _ < 1000 THEN UPDATE _ SET _ = _ * _; END IF; END; $$;

text: create a stored procedure in PLpgSQL to add Race_ID by para_Race_ID in race table if para_Race_ID is greater than 500.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_Race_ID integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF para_Race_ID > 500 THEN UPDATE "race" SET "Race_ID" = "Race_ID" + para_Race_ID; END IF; END; $$;
skeleton: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(_ _) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN IF _ > 500 THEN UPDATE _ SET _ = _ + _; END IF; END; $$;

text: create a procedure to increase each skill_id in Skills by para_skill_id - 100.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_skill_id integer) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN UPDATE "Skills" SET "skill_id" = "skill_id" + para_skill_id - 100; END; $$;

text: write a stored procedure in PLpgSQL to delete records from MediaType where MediaTypeId equals para_MediaTypeId and update Name to para_Name afterwards.
plsql: CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE sp(para_MediaTypeId integer, para_Name text) LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$ BEGIN DELETE FROM "MediaType" WHERE "MediaTypeId" = para_MediaTypeId; IF FOUND THEN UPDATE "MediaType" SET "Name" = para_Name; END IF; END; $$;
